FAQs
What are the benefits of studying at the First Faculty of Medicine, Charles University?
The faculty offers high-quality education, extensive clinical training, English-taught programs, research opportunities, and a diverse, multicultural environment.

How can Qadri-International help me study at Charles University?
Qadri-International provides comprehensive guidance, application assistance, visa support, financial planning, and pre-departure and post-arrival support to ensure a smooth study abroad experience.

Are there English-taught medical programs at Charles University?
Yes, the First Faculty of Medicine offers medical programs taught in English, making it accessible for international students.

What are the costs associated with studying at the First Faculty of Medicine?
Tuition fees range from €11,000 to €15,000 per year, and living expenses average between €400 and €800 per month. Scholarships and financial aid are available to help reduce these costs.

How do I apply to the First Faculty of Medicine?
The application process involves submitting an online application form, academic transcripts, a personal statement, letters of recommendation, and proof of language proficiency. Qadri-International can assist with each step of the application process.
